## Key Design Decisions

- **Design system:** teal-600 primary, teal-50 bg, Inter UI + DM Mono transcript/mono, bespoke healthcare palette (emerald clinical, amber live-call, red escalation) — no michaelwegter.com styling
- **Scripted fallback is the primary path:** keyword-based intent detection covers BOOK/FAQ/ESCALATE fully; WebLLM loads lazily on GPU-enabled browsers only
- **Inbound conversation machine:** 10 phases (greeting → intent → booking_who → booking_name → booking_reason → booking_time → booking_confirm → faq_topic → faq_follow → closing/escalating); all 3 intents have complete flows
- **Confidence threshold:** < 0.45 auto-escalates regardless of intent (matching researcher spec)
- **Pipeline viz:** 5 nodes (Greeting → Intent Detect → Booking/FAQ → Webhook → SMS) with emoji icons, light up sequentially in real time
- **SMS log:** appears in sidebar when booking confirmed (step 4); fires webhook step first then SMS step
- **Outbound:** 3 script types (appointment_reminder / reactivation_outreach / post_visit_followup) with contact.scriptVars highlighting teal; call auto-progresses with timed delays
- **Language toggle:** EN/ES conversation copy, FAQ responses, quick-reply chips all switch at App level; passed as prop to InboundCall + OutboundDialer
- **recharts chunk warning:** expected (604kB pre-gzip, 173kB gzip) — acceptable for demo, no code splitting needed

